{"TopicId":102739,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"How to make code or whatever?","CreatedByName":"HoloYolo","CreatedById":138353,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-26T20:15:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"HoloYolo","CreatedById":138353,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-26T20:15:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHi there, I just wanna make a simple as can be plugin for KSP. No parts whatsoever. Just to show how far you are from the KSC, Kerbin, or anywhere else. Problem is, how do you do it? Any help is appreciated.\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_kiss.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:kiss:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xannari Ferrows","CreatedById":125369,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-26T20:29:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIs it not easier just to whip out the 7th grade math book? \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00C3\u00A2\u00CB\u2020\u00C5\u00A1 \u003C/strong\u003E(Your distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E \u002B (Target object\u0027s distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust a little Pythagorean theorem.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HoloYolo","CreatedById":138353,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-26T20:32:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xannari Ferrows\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Xannari Ferrows\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIs it not easier just to whip out the 7th grade math book? \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00C3\u00A2\u00CB\u2020\u00C5\u00A1 \u003C/strong\u003E(Your distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E \u002B (Target object\u0027s distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust a little Pythagorean theorem.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003EWhy do math when you got a plugin?\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nightingale","CreatedById":119307,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-26T20:37:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xannari Ferrows\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Xannari Ferrows\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIs it not easier just to whip out the 7th grade math book? \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00C3\u00A2\u00CB\u2020\u00C5\u00A1 \u003C/strong\u003E(Your distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E \u002B (Target object\u0027s distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust a little Pythagorean theorem.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOr if you =\u0026gt; Kerbal =\u0026gt; Object don\u0027t make a right angle triangle (which is pretty much *always*):\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00C3\u00A2\u00CB\u2020\u00C5\u00A1 \u003C/strong\u003E(Your distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E \u002B (Target object\u0027s distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E - 2(Your distance to Kerbol)(Target\u0027s distance to Kerbol)*cos(\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/4/d/44ddf6e825ef5a1ea521e708af7deb73.png\u0022 alt=\u002244ddf6e825ef5a1ea521e708af7deb73.png\u0022\u003E)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhere \u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/4/d/44ddf6e825ef5a1ea521e708af7deb73.png\u0022 alt=\u002244ddf6e825ef5a1ea521e708af7deb73.png\u0022\u003E is the angle.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnyway, to answer OP\u0027s question - checkout the wiki\u0027s page on creating add-ons:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Plugins\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Plugins\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat being said, if you\u0027re going for as simple as possible, a code plugin probably isn\u0027t the answer - changing a part (either manually or via module manager) is \u003Cem\u003Evastly\u003C/em\u003E\u00C3\u00A2\u00E2\u201A\u00AC\u00E2\u20AC\u00B9 simpler.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-26T20:51:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xannari Ferrows\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Xannari Ferrows\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIs it not easier just to whip out the 7th grade math book? \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00C3\u00A2\u00CB\u2020\u00C5\u00A1 \u003C/strong\u003E(Your distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E \u002B (Target object\u0027s distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust a little Pythagorean theorem.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere\u0027s no guarantee that the triangle formed is a right triangle, so Pythagoras\u0027 Theorem very likely doesn\u0027t apply.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Greenfire32","CreatedById":36705,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-26T20:53:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xannari Ferrows\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Xannari Ferrows\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIs it not easier just to whip out the 7th grade math book? \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u00C3\u00A2\u00CB\u2020\u00C5\u00A1 \u003C/strong\u003E(Your distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E \u002B (Target object\u0027s distance to Kerbol)\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:10px;\u0022\u003E\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust a little Pythagorean theorem.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003EThis is miles higher than what I can understand. And I haven\u0027t been in school for like 6 years now...\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HoloYolo","CreatedById":138353,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-26T21:04:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EThere\u0027s no guarantee that the triangle formed is a right triangle, so Pythagoras\u0027 Theorem very likely doesn\u0027t apply.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003EThanks for moving this. I had a brainfart.\n"}]}